cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on the task of learning 3D object surface reconstructions from single RGB images, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning approach, which involves designing a deep architecture and using different shape representations, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with complex topologies, which suggests that it may fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses a stage-wise learning approach, which could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
